sentences: Thomas James Schuyler (born June 10, 1952, in Bethlehem, Pennsylvania) is an American songwriter.
In 1983, Schuyler signed to Capitol Records and released the album Brave Heart.
Its title track was a No. 43 single on the Hot Country Singles (now Hot Country Songs) charts.
He also headed RCA Records' Nashville division from 1992 to 1995.
Schuyler is currently the Young Adult Minister at a church in Nashville and is an adjunct instructor at Belmont University.
